Project2

Class Stack

  • java.lang.Object
    • Project2.Stack

  • public class Stack
extends java.lang.Object
    2.Create a class named Stack that will implement a stack of state objects using an array. Support the following methods.

    [Stack(int)] a. Constructor that creates the stack array based on a size provided.

    [push(State)] b. A push method to push a state on the stack

    [pop()] c. A pop method to pop a state off the stack and return it.

    [printStack()] d. A printStack method to print the stack, see the example.

    [isEmpty()] e. An isEmpty method that returns true if the stack is empty, false otherwise

    [isFull()] f. An isFull method that returns true if the stack is full, false otherwise

    Version:
    10/13/17
    Author:
    Ryan Geddings N01067534

        public void printStack()
        Method has no return. Method prints out the stack header, then iterates through the stack, object by object. For each object it calls the State.toString() override to convert the object into a formatted string.
